    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl>Morelli in <ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>261</citedRange> (no image)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>105100</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-62867"><name nymRef="#Ἀνδροκλῆς">Ἀνδροκλῆς</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65090"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Νεῦσσος">Νεύσσω</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Androklès fils de Neussos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Androkles son of Neussos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Androkles figlio di Neussos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>أندروكليس بن نيوسوس</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The position of the stele, partly hidden by other stones, forbade to make a photograph.</p>
	<p>The name <foreign xml:lang="grc">Νεῦσσος</foreign>, from the dialectal form of the word 'nestling', is not quite uncommon at Cyrene.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
